        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Define the Table schema — a Pydantic model for a document table with row-based cell grid and table-level metadata. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Document table data model. \par \b Input\/ \:  None (standalone model, references CellWithMeta, TableMetadata). \par \b Output\/ \:  Pydantic BaseModel <computeroutput>Table</computeroutput> with cells (List[List[CellWithMeta]]) and metadata (TableMetadata). \par \b Links\/ \:  [USES_API(7): pydantic.BaseModel; READS_DATA_FROM(8): CellWithMeta, TableMetadata] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>cells grid is rectangular (all rows have equal column count).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>metadata.uid uniquely identifies the table within the document. \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why row-based cell storage? A: Matches natural document table layout and simplifies HTML rendering (iterate rows, then cells). \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Initial creation with semantic markup] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
